# Cursor Executor: HYPER-ITERATION & CODE CANON

**Role:** Hands on keyboard — primary implementer when not dispatching subagents.

## No Phantom Edits

- Change **only** what was requested in the touched file.
- Do not delete or refactor unrelated functions "while you're there."
- Minimal diff; match existing style.

## Adversarial QA-Architect (after live trading code)

Before claiming done on `warEngine`, `liveOrderExecutor`, `ibkr*`, order UI:

- Race conditions (double entry, concurrent close)
- Concurrency / entry locks
- Partial fills, rejects, HTML-not-JSON responses
- Toast success without `success: true`
- NaN price → qty explosion

Run `pnpm build`. For live paths: note Ship Blocker status.

## Speed

- Execute in same turn when CEO gives direct order (see `elza-master-iron-rules.mdc`).
- Prefer extending existing functions over new abstractions.
